<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1756,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">
The comparison of the taxonomic classifications shows that there are important differences in the number of Chilean genera and species (
<tableCitation box="[456,540,1792,1818]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Taxonomic diversity of the Chilean cacti according to three classifications." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF6F6659FFE5FFB7FF30068EFB80FF74" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" tableUuid="DF6F6659FFE5FFB7FF30068EFB80FF74">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Hunt’s classification (2006, 2013, 2016) includes the lowest number of species (95), whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, R. &amp; Marticorena, C. &amp; Alarcon, D. &amp; Baeza, C. &amp; Cavieres, V. &amp; Finot, L. &amp; Fuentes, N. &amp; Kiessling, A. &amp; Mihoc, M. &amp; Pauchard, A. &amp; Ruiz, E. &amp; Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A." box="[292,549,1828,1854]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 430" refId="ref18598" refString="Rodriguez, R., Marticorena, C., Alarcon, D., Baeza, C., Cavieres, V., Finot, L., Fuentes, N., Kiessling, A., Mihoc, M., Pauchard, A., Ruiz, E., Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A. (2018) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Chile. Gayana Botanica 75: 1 - 430. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4067 / S 0717 - 66432018000100001" type="journal article" year="2018">
Rodríguez 
<emphasis box="[415,469,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
reports the lowest number of genera (17). The percentage of endemic species also varies: 73% by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. &amp; Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G." box="[308,500,1864,1891]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" refId="ref17156" refString="Hunt, D., Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G. (2006) The New Cactus Lexicon. DH Books, Milborn Port, 526 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Hunt 
<emphasis box="[371,426,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">et al.</emphasis>
(2006
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. &amp; Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G." box="[510,569,1864,1890]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" refId="ref17187" refString="Hunt, D., Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G. (2013) The New Cactus Lexicon, Atlas of Illustrations. Dh Books, Milborn Port, 373 pp." type="book" year="2013">2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D." box="[579,639,1864,1891]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" refId="ref17134" refString="Hunt, D. (2016) CITES Cactaceae Checklist Third Edition. Milborne Port, Remous Limited, 175 pp." type="book" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
), 74% by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, R. &amp; Marticorena, C. &amp; Alarcon, D. &amp; Baeza, C. &amp; Cavieres, V. &amp; Finot, L. &amp; Fuentes, N. &amp; Kiessling, A. &amp; Mihoc, M. &amp; Pauchard, A. &amp; Ruiz, E. &amp; Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A." box="[749,1010,1864,1890]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 430" refId="ref18598" refString="Rodriguez, R., Marticorena, C., Alarcon, D., Baeza, C., Cavieres, V., Finot, L., Fuentes, N., Kiessling, A., Mihoc, M., Pauchard, A., Ruiz, E., Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A. (2018) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Chile. Gayana Botanica 75: 1 - 430. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4067 / S 0717 - 66432018000100001" type="journal article" year="2018">
Rodríguez 
<emphasis box="[872,928,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
, 81% in the present study. These results highlight the importance of updating the taxonomic classifications in the Flora of 
<collectingCountry box="[1058,1121,1900,1926]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Chile</collectingCountry>
, because underestimating the endemism and number of species may have major negative effects on conservation (see e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Mace, G. M." box="[1174,1302,1936,1963]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="711 - 719" refId="ref17884" refString="Mace, G. M. (2004) The role of taxonomy in species conservation. Philosophical transactions of the Royal Society of London. Series B, Biological sciences 359: 711 - 719. https: // doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 2003.1454" type="journal article" year="2004">Mace 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Duarte, M. &amp; Guerrero, P. C. &amp; Carvallo, G. &amp; Bustamante, R. O." pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="236 - 242" refId="ref16409" refString="Duarte, M., Guerrero, P. C., Carvallo, G. &amp; Bustamante, R. O. (2014) Conservation network design for endemic cacti under taxonomic uncertainty. Biological Conservation 176: 236 - 242." type="journal article" year="2014">
Duarte 
<emphasis box="[1396,1452,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). The number of species accepted here means that the 
<taxonomicName box="[799,912,1972,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cactaceae</taxonomicName>
represent 6% of the Chilean native angiosperms and 5% of endemic species of 
<collectingCountry box="[478,539,2008,2034]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, R. &amp; Marticorena, C. &amp; Alarcon, D. &amp; Baeza, C. &amp; Cavieres, V. &amp; Finot, L. &amp; Fuentes, N. &amp; Kiessling, A. &amp; Mihoc, M. &amp; Pauchard, A. &amp; Ruiz, E. &amp; Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A." box="[553,803,2008,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 430" refId="ref18598" refString="Rodriguez, R., Marticorena, C., Alarcon, D., Baeza, C., Cavieres, V., Finot, L., Fuentes, N., Kiessling, A., Mihoc, M., Pauchard, A., Ruiz, E., Sanchez, P. &amp; Marticorena, A. (2018) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Chile. Gayana Botanica 75: 1 - 430. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4067 / S 0717 - 66432018000100001" type="journal article" year="2018">
Rodríguez 
<emphasis box="[679,735,2008,2034]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
